# React Conventions

## Components
- Functional components with hooks only
- Props via explicit `interface` (not inline types)
- Use `memo()` for components that don't need frequent re-renders
- Export as named export: `export function ChatInput() { ... }`

```typescript
interface ChatInputProps {
    onSend: (message: string) => void;
    isLoading?: boolean;
}

export const ChatInput = memo(function ChatInput({ onSend, isLoading }: ChatInputProps) {
    // ...
});
```

## Hooks
- Prefix with `use`, return objects (not arrays)
- Wrap callbacks in `useCallback` when passed as props

```typescript
export function useDiagnosisChat() {
    // ...
    return { messages, status, error, sendMessage };
}
```

## File Structure
Each component gets its own directory:
```
components/
  ChatInput/
    index.tsx     # Component
    styles.ts     # antd-style createStyles
```
